Key Match Events: Travis Head's 76 kept Australia in the game
India will face England in the semi-finals
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia's World Cup hopes are hanging by a thread
Others: Indian captain Rohit Sharma was named the Player of the Match
Josh Hazlewood was able to slow India down
Australia lost an edging David Warner in the first over of the chase
Mitch Marsh offered hope of a captain's knock with 37 from 28 balls
Glenn Maxwell also threatened to provide Head the support he needed
Australia lost 5-54 from that point on as none of their middle order below No.4 Maxwell fired
The result means the undefeated India qualify for the semi-finals
